Job Title: Senior Analyst - Operational Intelligence - Cyber Intelligence
Ad Text:
We are looking for a Senior Analyst to join the operational intelligence capability within CyberCX Intelligence. Be part of a dynamic, high-performing team with unparalleled visibility into our region's cyber threat landscape. Our ideal candidate will value a highly collegiate environment, have excellent analysis skills and strong foundations in both cyber threat intelligence and technical cyber concepts. You'll thrive in a fast-paced environment and be able to work both within a multidisciplinary team and proactively, under limited direction.
  
About the team
CyberCX Intelligence is a dedicated intelligence capability, with experts in tactical, operational and strategic intelligence. Situated inside one of the world’s largest end-to-end cyber security companies, we have the information, access and context to help our customers to make better decisions at all levels: from threat hunts and cyber exercises, to incident response, remediation and uplift activities.
  
How you’ll make an impact
As a Senior Analyst, you will make a tangible impact to the security of organisations in Australia and globally. You will provide real-time intelligence support to high-profile cyber incidents, lead intelligence investigations to proactively uncover threats to our customers, and monitor the threat landscape to find new insights about threat actors and their techniques. You will also apply these assessments to real-world situations, through intelligence-led threat hunts, adversary simulations, tabletop exercises, threat profile assessments and more.

Day to day you will:

Monitor the global and regional threat landscape to identify and action threat information relevant to our customers.
Collect, triage and synthesise information from multiple sources, which you build and validate. 
Extend your subject matter expertise in threat actor techniques and capabilities and in threat intelligence concepts such as MITRE ATT&CK.
Write short form intelligence SITREPs and advisories, often under time pressure, for cyber practitioners and longer form threat actor profiles and intelligence reports for business leaders.
Lead intelligence investigations, aggregating threat information from across Incident Response case files, as well as dark web and other open source investigations.
Lead, coach and mentor Associate Analysts and Analysts from diverse backgrounds and with diverse skillsets.
Key skills and attributes

Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills with a demonstrated ability to analyse and amalgamate diverse information to identify trends, patterns and insights.
Excellent understanding of the region’s cyber threat landscape and of cyber threat intelligence frameworks and processes.
Strong communication skills, with the ability to produce oral and written products with structure, clarity and precision.
Stakeholder engagement and project management skills and a track record of delivering results in high-pressure environments.
Experience and qualifications

3-5 years’ relevant professional experience, with experience in intelligence and consulting both highly regarded.
Minimum Bachelor’s degree.
Australian citizenship is required 
What's in it for you?

Flexible working in a hybrid arrangement (a blend of office and WFH).
A high-performing, collegiate team with a commitment to continuous learning.
A dynamic environment where no day is the same, and you make a difference to customers and communities.
Once-in-a-career growth opportunities.
Attractive salary and employee benefits package.

NB. Due to Christmas Holidays Applicants will be reviewed week commencing 6th January ***

Ad Text:
Job Description

Our Connected Technology Group (CTG) defines and drives the digital, data and technology strategy for KPMG. We have an important advocacy role for technology in the market and across KPMG, working with our technology leaders to build our market presence. We cultivate collaboration and integrate tech execution across our business, driving a firmwide approach to how we go-to-market and build the capability of our people and attract new talent. 

Your Opportunity

The role of Senior Data Engineer in the CTG Data & Analytics platforms team at KPMG Australia involves designing, building, and optimising modern data platforms, with a focus on Microsoft Fabric. This position plays a critical role in developing Enterprise Data Platform ingestion frameworks and patterns to support advanced analytics and business intelligence. Responsibilities include ensuring scalability, security, and performance for various business unit use cases, as well as contributing to the creation of centralised data agents, API end points for Data objects in MS Fabric, to drive the firm's data strategy.

The key requirements for a Senior Data Engineer role in the context of designing and implementing end-to-end data solutions using Microsoft Fabric, while ensuring data quality, security, and governance, include:

Expertise in Data Platform build:

Proficiency in tools like MS Fabric/Databricks including OneLake, Delta Lakehouse architecture, Data Factory, PySpark, and Power BI to design and implement scalable data solutions.

Experience in building and optimising data ingestion pipelines for structured, semi-structured, and unstructured data.

Data Quality Assurance:

Develop and implement robust data validation and cleansing processes.

Use metadata-driven, reusable frameworks for data processing and orchestration.

Designed and Build Patterns for Entity resolution, Quality, Tagging to ensure accuracy and reliability.

Data Security:

Implement role-based access control (RBAC), encryption, and compliance with enterprise security standards.

Regularly audit and monitor access logs to detect and mitigate vulnerabilities.

Data Governance and Lineage:

Implement enterprise-wide governance policies, including data classification, ownership, and stewardship defined by Data Governance team.

Use tools like Microsoft Purview for managing and governing data assets.

Implement automated lineage tracking to ensure transparency and traceability of data flows.

Collaboration and Stakeholder Engagement:

Partner with business stakeholders, data analysts, reporting team and data scientists to deliver trusted datasets.

Foster a data-centric culture by training stakeholders on governance practises and the importance of data integrity.

Performance Optimisation:

Lead performance tuning and cost optimisation for Microsoft Fabric environments.

Design scalable architectures to handle growing data volumes and complex analytics use cases.

DevOps and Automation:

Drive the adoption of modern DevOps, CI/CD, and automation practises within data engineering workflows.

Mentorship and Leadership:

Mentor junior engineers and contribute to the data engineering community of practise.

These requirements ensure the delivery of secure, reliable, and scalable data solutions aligned with enterprise standards, enabling advanced analytics and business intelligence.

How are you extraordinary?

You enjoy working in the details, with a positive and proactive attitude towards accuracy and deadlines.

You get things done! You’re organised, efficient, and have a high attention to detail to deliver impactful outcomes.

You are passionate about the importance of fantastic communication to share ideas, inspire, and create change. You are able to digest, distill, and communicate complex concepts in both written and verbal forms.

Your Experience

At KPMG, we believe diversity of thought, background and experience strengthens relationships and delivers meaningful benefits to our people, our clients, and communities. To be considered for this opportunity, your qualifications, skills & experience could include:

Proven experience (10+ years) in data engineering, cloud data platforms, and analytics solutions.

Hands-on expertise with Microsoft Fabric or Databricks, including OneLake, Lakehouse, Data Factory, Synapse, and Power BI integration.

Strong proficiency in SQL, PySpark, and data modeling (dimensional, lakehouse, and semantic models).

Experience implementing data governance, cataloging, and lineage frameworks.

Familiarity with metadata-driven frameworks and automation patterns.

Strong understanding of ETL/ELT, streaming, batch data pipelines, and API-based ingestion.

Solid grasp of data security, compliance, and access management.

Exposure to Azure ecosystem (Azure Data Lake, Databricks, Purview, Azure DevOps) is highly desirable.

Excellent problem-solving, communication, and stakeholder management skills.

Prior experience in large-scale enterprise data transformation programs

Experience working in Agile delivery models.

Qualifications

We are looking for applicants that have:

Microsoft certifications (e.g., Fabric Analytics Engineer Associate, Azure Data Engineer Associate).

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Job Description

Our Finance Transformation team are trusted advisors to CFOs and their Finance teams supporting them to meet the challenges of a complex and rapidly evolving business environment. We help them navigate change to deliver efficiency, insight and value to their businesses. Our diverse and multidisciplinary team brings together skill sets across Finance.

The role we specifically require is within the Finance Transformation service offering. Finance Transformation is a strategic assessment of an organisation’s finance operating model including systems, processes, people and operations, aimed at increasing efficiency and effectiveness, enhancing decision-making, and aligning financial functions with broader business objectives using digital technologies and other improvements.

Your Opportunity:

With continued growth and strong pipeline, we are now seeking a Director to join our team, with a focus to managing Finance Transformation engagements across ERP and EPM solutions covering planning, budgeting and forecasting, reporting (Performance and Financial), data analytics and insights, and integration of AI in Finance. Alongside delivering exceptional client outcomes, you will drive business development activities by building strong relationships and identifying new opportunities.

You will work with some of the country’s leading clients as well as the wider national team, in a positive, collaborative and team focused environment. This role is ideally suited to candidates who have prior finance transformation experience as well as experience leading cross-functional teams ideally in a Consulting environment or in a transformation capacity, and who are seeking an opportunity to broaden their experience working with different clients, as well as undertaking challenging and rewarding work harnessing their leadership, analytical and problem-solving skills.

Experience and Skills

Recent experience managing in areas of finance operations, shared services, financial planning & analysis, and accounting ideally in a consulting environment or in a transformation program.

Deep understanding of how a system implementation project is delivered (e.g. phases, core teams, standard deliverables).

Advanced ERP / EPM / Cloud technology experience through previous engagements or industry experience (e.g. Oracle. Microsoft, SAP).

Ability to articulate functional business requirements to technical requirements and facilitate solution design and development.

Excellent verbal and analytical skills with the ability to write at a client-ready quality level

Bachelor's degree in an appropriate field from an accredited college/university

About Us

At Red Energy, we are passionate about providing award-winning customer service to over 1.5 million of our customers across the country. Owned by the mighty Snowy Hydro, we are 100% Australian owned which our customers love us for. Our award winning team have won 14 consecutive Canstar Blue Awards for best overall customer satisfaction amongst Victorian electricity providers. Looking for a career change? Join an award-winning team passionate about exceptional customer service!

About the Role

Ready to be the key driver in a major business transformation for an iconic Australian energy company? You will play a pivotal role in the design, development, and delivery of Financial reporting requirements for our new Core Retail Platform (CRP). You will be the crucial link between the Finance team and the Technology Implementation team, ensuring all financial data and reporting is robust and that Finance is well prepared for future reporting and analysis. This is a full-time fixed term role for the duration of the project based in Melbourne. 

Key Responsibilities

Champion the design, development, and configuration of Finance requirements for the new Core Retail Platform (CRP) and its supporting applications.
Conduct end-to-end Finance requirements mapping in consultation with stakeholders, and write functional specifications that align with Finance objectives.
Navigate complex data structures and system logic to deliver accurate, Retail energy-specific Finance reporting requirements.
Proactively research and problem-solve challenges, particularly those involving estimation and judgement.
Coordinate and execute testing activities to ensure all financial system, data, and reporting outputs meet defined business requirements and expectations
Manage the integration of new solutions into existing Finance processes to ensure a seamless implementation and minimal business impact.
Develop complete and accurate finance-related documentation, including process flows and training materials, for a successful project handover.

What You’ll Bring to the Role

Tertiary qualifications in Commerce, Accounting, Finance, or Information Technology.
Mandatory experience working within the Retail Energy industry, with specific knowledge of financial/accounting processes unique to the sector.
Minimum of 5 years experience as a Business Analyst, with at least 3 years focused on finance transformation projects (ERP, Billing, or major platform implementation).
Exceptional ability to communicate technical concepts to finance stakeholders and financial requirements to technical developers.
Highly analytical and detail-oriented, with a proven ability to manage complex scope and competing priorities.
Strong ability to independently collect and analyse data (SQL Skills highly regarded).
Proven competencies in: financial analysis, problem solving, attention to detail, adaptability, and excellent communication.

This is your chance to play a pivotal role in a major business transformation from the ground up. If you're ready to bring your energy, ideas, and initiative into a team that values Ownership, Teamwork, and Agility — we’d love to hear from you. Apply today and help shape the future of energy in Australia.

Ad Text:
Job Description

Is your career focused on analysing and determining true business value?

Do you bring leadership, commercial acumen, and advanced modelling skills to solve complex valuation challenges?

KPMG’s Valuation Services team supports clients across all industries with robust, independent valuations. Valuations that support strategic decisions, whether for transactions, acquisitions, joint ventures, shareholder resolutions, investments, or regulatory and financial reporting requirements.

Why Join Us?

Our Valuation Services team is part of the broader Deal Advisory and Infrastructure group. We are recognised for technical expertise, a collaborative culture, and delivering high-quality outcomes that make a measurable impact for clients.

Based in Perth, you’ll work in one of Australia’s most dynamic markets. Western Australia generates around 17% of the national economy with only 10% of the population, driven by its strength in resources, energy, and infrastructure. This scale creates exceptional opportunities for high-value transactions and strategic advisory work with both domestic and cross-border clients, all while living in a world-class beachside city known for its stunning coastline, outdoor lifestyle, and outstanding quality of life.

Your Opportunity – Associate Director

The Perth valuation practice is expanding to meet strong market demand, creating opportunities for experienced professionals to join our team. In this role, you will:

Identify key performance indicators and value drivers across companies, industries, and transactions.

Deliver clear, insightful valuation reports that explain assumptions, methodologies, and findings.

Build, review, and interpret financial models for businesses and projects.

Apply critical thinking to identify issues and collaborate with colleagues across Deal Advisory.

Engage with clients to understand business performance, cash flow forecasts, and valuation drivers.

Use both traditional and innovative valuation methodologies to assess the value of assets, equity, and debt instruments.

How are You Extraordinary?

You are a curious and analytical thinker who enjoys uncovering insights and presenting them clearly.

You bring experience or a strong interest in delivering valuation advice that influences strategic decisions.

You are detail-oriented leader able to manage teams of skilled professionals, takes a proactive approach, and is committed to accuracy and meeting deadlines.

You thrive in a collaborative environment with the ability to solve problems and adapt to challenges.

You are eager to learn how to prepare client materials such as proposals and pitch packs, and you’re open to developing these skills.

Your Experience

At KPMG, we believe that diversity of thought, background, and experience drives better outcomes for our people, clients, and communities. We welcome applications from individuals with:

Demonstrated experience in business valuations (including Purchase Price Allocations / PPA, Intangible valuations, tax valuations etc.) or corporate finance within a corporate advisory or professional services environment.

Relevant degree (i.e. commerce, finance, economics) and ideally (but not essential) working towards or considering postgraduate studies (e.g., CA, CFA).

A commercial mindset, resilience, and a drive to improve processes and outcomes.

Strong analytical and report writing skills, with the ability to simplify complex information.

Proven experience building and maintaining financial models and delivering Excel-based financial analysis.

Excellent interpersonal skills and the ability to build trusted relationships, including mentoring junior team members.

Strong project management skills, with a track record of delivering multiple engagements simultaneously.

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth.

Reporting to a Commercial Finance Manager, you'll partner closely with supply chain, technology, digital and broader business teams, providing commercial insight, financial analysis and decision support across planning, reporting, budgeting and projects.

Experience improving financial processes and systems

Authentic, inclusive and collaborative

You have an opportunity to personally thrive, make a difference and be part of a culture where individuality is noticed and valued every day.

In this role, you will play a pivotal role in understanding and improving our business processes and systems, helping us make informed decisions to drive organizational success. You will play an important part in the deployment of the new solution, supporting the Solutions Director across multiple streams of work.

Role Responsibilities:

Collaborate with stakeholders to elicit and document business requirements, ensuring a deep understanding of business needs and objectives.

Document and model current and future business processes to identify areas for improvement and optimization.

Conduct meetings and presentations to share ideas and findings.

Document and communicate the results of individual efforts.

Effectively communicate insights and plans to cross-functional team members and management.

Ensure solutions meet business needs and requirements.

Solid experience in business analysis

About the role

An exciting new opportunity has become available for a Business Analyst to join our Integrated Portfolio Planning division on a 12-month assignment.
The Trading Technology team is the primary interface between AGL Technology and Integrated Energy's Trading & Integrated Portfolio Planning teams, as well as the Wholesale Risk and Finance teams.

Working closely with the Physical Markets Team who are responsible for managing AGL's electricity and gas procurement position. You will facilitate system and process changes and improvements that enable the Trading team to respond quickly to the market conditions and optimize the execution of physical trading strategies.

Key responsibilities

Business process mapping of complex systems and stakeholder dependencies
Supporting the analysis and requirements gathering process for front end development and data intensive products.
Implementation of complex engineering methodology and market rules to optimise physical trading outcomes across physical power, gas and FCAS markets.
Run and facilitate workshops to gather and document requirements for both business and technical stakeholders.
Analyse existing systems and processes to identify impacts, changes and opportunities.
Build and manage stakeholder relationships with a variety of different business units.
Assist delivery teams with the coordination of planning ceremonies.


About you

You are an established Business Analyst with a user-centered mindset who is comfortable with building relationships with a wide range of stakeholders ranging from delivery teams to senior leaders. Your ability to successfully map complex business processes and understand the 'bigger picture' of how systems interact will ensure your success in this role.

In addition to the above you will demonstrate:

Experience working to deliver complex initiatives end-to-end in an agile environment.
Experience applying different techniques to elicit business requirements.
Ability to balance multiple competing priorities and effectively manage expectations.
Excellent communication skills, both written and oral.
Ability to facilitate workshops to drive outcomes and solve problems between multiple parties.
Experience working with energy trading organisational functions such as trading (Forward, physical, origination) & an understanding of the Australian energy markets and emerging challenges are highly regarded.

Who We Are

iSelect and Compare the Market are trusted, well-known brands dedicated to helping millions of Australians compare and buy personal finance and household products such as insurance, energy, and loans. Together, we provide a seamless, customer-focused experience that makes it easier for Australians to find the right products to suit their needs.

What You’ll Be Doing

Governance isn’t a tick-box exercise here - it’s part of our DNA. You’ll lead the design and delivery of our enterprise-wide Data Governance Framework - an initiative that underpins our entire technology roadmap and informs decisions at every level of the organization. You’ll also be an enabler for enterprise projects, creating usable, explainable frameworks that support real outcomes and influence critical KRIs that shape how data drives our decision-making.

You’ll be responsible for leading the implementation and ongoing management of our Data Governance Framework. This includes defining strategy, objectives, roles and responsibilities, shared definitions, policies, standards, procedures, and technologies to support informed, data-driven decision-making as well as control and mitigate data risks across the business

Your focus will be to:

Define and implement strategy, objectives and standards that make data governance practical and impactful
Drive end-to-end initiatives across data cataloguing, data quality, literacy and security
Champion data governance adoption by educating and empowering teams across the business
Translate complex technical concepts into clear, actionable frameworks for both technical and non-technical stakeholders

This is a high-profile role with visibility at Board level, ensuring our governance program stays on track and delivers measurable value. You’ll work within a multi-disciplinary team that brings together Governance, Analytics and Reporting - giving you variety in a highly collaborative environment!

What’s In It For You

At Compare the Market and iSelect, we’re all about helping people make smart choices – and joining us might just be yours. We offer an environment where your ideas are heard, your contributions are valued, and your growth genuinely matters. Collaboration is part of our DNA, and you’ll be joining a supportive, forward-thinking team where you can do meaningful work (and be recognised for it!) 

We’re guided by three shared values that shape how we work, how we treat each other, and how we show up for our customers - Drive, Noble Intent and All Together.

Plus, we offer a range of great perks to help you thrive both in and out of work:

Enjoy flexible work arrangements, including the option of one day working from home each week or a 9-day fortnight
Enjoy additional leave days - ‘ME’ leave and ‘Volunteer Day’ leave
Option to purchase additional leave
Return To Work bonus for returning parents
Quarterly Award and Recognition program

What Sets You Apart

You’re someone who knows data governance inside out and loves making it practical, not just theoretical. With a solid foundation in the principles and standards that keep data safe and useful, you’re confident working with senior stakeholders and influencing decisions. You will also have experience working with one or more popular data governance tools (Informatica, Collibra, Alation etc) along with hands on implementation of the same across an enterprise landscape.

Communication is your superpower - you can turn technical jargon into plain language and bring people on the journey. Above all, you’re collaborative, solutions-focused and ready to lead initiatives that make a real impact. You’ll also have:

 Around 5+ years in data governance or data management (you know your stuff!)
Developed KPIs and dashboards to measure the effectiveness of data governance initiatives.
Worked closely with data stewards, business data owners, IT stakeholders to educate on data governance policies and standards.
Solid understanding of standards like ISO/IEC 38505, CPG235, DMBOK, AESCSF, ISO 27001 and GDPR
Defined and implemented data quality framework, processes and enabled data quality uplift 
DAMA certification or accreditation? This is a big plus
Proven experience leading people (directly and virtually) and managing resources
Comfortable rolling up your sleeves and working independently 

Sound like a good fit? Let’s talk!

Support enterprise-wide change impacting a broad user base

8+ years SBA experience within highly governed organisations (ideally banking, government, commerce etc)

Strong business process and change delivery background

Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills

Comfortable influencing and driving change in complex environments

Consulting and banking background highly desirable

This is a fantastic opportunity to work closely with a passionate and collaborative project team, responsible for analysing, designing, and implementing business processes to improve efficiency and effectiveness. If you're someone who thrives in a fast-paced, complex environment and enjoys problem-solving and improving how we work, we’d love to hear from you.

Job Title: Senior Business Improvement and Change Manager
Ad Text:
Senior Business Improvement and Change Manager

Fixed term, full time, 12 months with possible extension.

West Leederville

Over the last 70 years Relationships Australia WA has been providing relationship support services for individuals, couples, families and communities. We are a team of professional and highly motivated staff who are committed to enhancing the lives of communities, families and individuals and supporting positive and respectful relationships.

About the role

We are seeking a Senior Business Improvement and Change Manager to join our West Leederville Corporate office for a fixed term. Play a pivotal role in ensuring the success of our digital transformation by optimising service delivery processes and leading organisational change for over 300 staff and 15,000+ clients. This role bridges technical implementation and operational adoption within an Agile Scrum team. The current vacancy is 37.5 hours per week.

Skills, experience, and qualifications

Core Responsibilities

Business Improvement & Process Optimisation

Map current state processes and collaboratively design future state workflows that leverage new technology.

Enlist and enable internal business improvement champions to drive process optimisation across locations.

Change Management

Design and execute comprehensive change management strategies, including stakeholder analysis, impact assessments, and readiness plans.

Develop targeted communications and engagement activities to build awareness and knowledge across the staff base.

Evidence-Based Decision Making

Utilise evidence-based management frameworks to measure value, identify gaps, and validate improvements.

Monitor adoption metrics post-release and iterate on support mechanisms to ensure sustained change.

Training & Capability

Define training requirements and oversee the creation of support materials to ensure staff proficiency with new systems.

Team & Culture Contributions

Operate as a core member of the Scrum team, integrating change management and process improvement into the development lifecycle.

Champion agile practices and foster an environment of psychological safety, creativity, and experimentation.

Support consensus-based decisions grounded in evidence and expertise.

Uphold organisational values: Authenticity, Inclusivity, Compassion, and Excellence.

Qualifications and Experience:

Tertiary qualifications in Business, IT, Organisational Psychology, or related discipline, or equivalent professional experience.

Minimum 5 years’ experience in Business Improvement or Change Management roles within technology transformation projects.

Demonstrated experience working effectively within Agile/Scrum delivery teams.

Key Selection Criteria - Knowledge:

Deep understanding of change management principles (PROSCI/ADKAR highly regarded).

Strong knowledge of process improvement methodologies (Lean Six Sigma highly regarded).

Working knowledge of Agile/Scrum and evidence-based management.

Key Selection Criteria - Skills and Experience:

Proven ability to work autonomously and take ownership of change strategy.

Exceptional interpersonal skills and ability to influence stakeholders at all levels.

A current Working with Children Check and WA Police Force National Police Check to obtain upon required)

Applications close at 4pm, 21 January 2026

Job Title: Head of Bus. Partnering & Analysis | Engineering Tech. Solns
Ad Text:
Ref: A000909

Hands on Cost Optimisation & Performance Improvement
Key Stakeholder Leadership
Support business optimisation and M&A growth

The Company

Robert Half Executive Search has been retained to appoint a commercially savvy and hands-on Head of Business Partnering & Analysis for a growing Engineering Technology Solutions as part of a growing global group.

Our client is a market leader in the design, manufacture, and distribution of innovative ventilation solutions. From large-scale industrial HVAC systems to residential acoustic solutions, this group is renowned for engineering excellence.

With a substantial manufacturing footprint across Australia, New Zealand, and South East Asia, this group provides critical infrastructure technology that improves both air quality and energy efficiency.

The Role

Reporting directly to the Regional Finance Director, this highly visible impact role is well suited to a hands on finance leader who is both data and insights driven.

You will act as the primary intermediary between Finance and the broader business-specifically Manufacturing, Operations, and Sales-ensuring that every technical and operational decision is backed by rigorous financial logic and a focus on bottom-line productivity.

Key Responsibilities & Focus Areas

Cost Optimisation & Efficiency: Conduct deep-dive analysis into manufacturing costs, supply chain overheads, and operational wastage. Implement frameworks to drive lean financial performance.
Strategic FP&A & Modelling: Lead the end-to-end budgeting and forecasting process. You will be expected to build and refine complex financial models that provide "real-time" insight into business health.
Stakeholder Partnering: Act as a "constructive challenger" to the Leadership Team and Operations Managers. You will translate complex production and sales data into actionable strategies for non-financial stakeholders.
Hands-on Performance Management: Monitor KPIs and variances across the transactional landscape. You will be responsible for ensuring accountability across various business units.
Systems & Continuous Improvement: Take a lead role in enhancing financial systems and Excel-based tools to increase reporting speed and reliability.

What You Will Bring

Qualifications: Tertiary degree in Finance/Commerce with a CA or CPA qualification.
FP&A Expertise: Proven experience in a senior FP&A or Business Partnering role, ideally within a Manufacturing, Engineering, or Industrial environment.
Hands-on Mentality: You enjoy getting into the "weeds" of the data. You are not just a reviewer; you are a creator of models and a seeker of detail.
Technical Mastery: Expert-level Excel skills are non-negotiable. You must be comfortable building complex models from scratch to support on-demand planning.
Commercial Acumen: A track record of identifying cost-saving initiatives and successfully partnering with operational leads to implement them.
Influence: The ability to communicate the "why" behind the numbers to production managers and sales directors alike.

Why Join this group?

This is rare opportunity to join a technically sophisticated, stable, yet evolving Australian enterprise. You will have a seat at the table to influence the financial direction of a regional leader during a period of continued innovation and growth.

Apply Today

Please send your resume by clicking on the apply button.

Your application will be assessed within 3-5 working days. Please note only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

Learn more about our recruitment services: https://www.roberthalf.com.au/contact-us

Job Title: Senior Technical Data Solutions Architect / Delivery Lead
Ad Text:
Sunstone Advisory has an opportunity to support a Defence client seeking Senior Technical Data Solutions Architect / Delivery Lead. The Senior Technical Data Solutions Architect / Delivery Lead is a hybrid leadership role responsible for the design, oversight, and delivery of complex data analytics solutions within the Defence environment.

The primary purpose of this role is to act as the authoritative bridge between senior business stakeholders (ADF/APS) and technical development teams. The incumbent will translate operational requirements into robust technical architectures and direct the development of end-to-end data services, ensuring solutions are fit-for-purpose, secure, and accurate.

Estimated start date is late January/early February 2026.

This role is based in Canberra, ACT.

Candidates must be an Australian Citizen and already hold a current AGSVA NV1 Security Clearance (NV2 highly desirable) to commence work in this role. Please clearly indicate the current level held within your responses.

Key Accountabilities
Technical Solution Design & Architecture

 * Lead the architectural design of end-to-end data solutions, encompassing data ingestion, storage, modelling, and visualisation.

 * Define and enforce design patterns for the Teradata (Data Warehouse) and Power BI (Visualisation) stack.

 * Develop strategies for integrating data from multiple, disparate, and legacy Defence systems into a unified "Single Source of Truth."

 * Ensure all data designs adhere to Departmental security, governance, and architectural standards.

Technical Delivery & Team Leadership

 * Direct and manage the day-to-day activities of technical teams (Data Engineers, BI Developers), assigning tasks and managing sprint priorities.

 * Oversee the build quality of data products, ensuring code is efficient, maintainable, and scalable.

 * Act as the technical escalation point for the team, resolving complex blockers related to data lineage, performance tuning, or integration failures.

Stakeholder Management & Requirements Translation

 * Serve as the primary conduit between non-technical stakeholders and the engineering squad.

 * Translate complex military/operational requirements into precise technical specifications and acceptance criteria for developers.

 * Manage stakeholder expectations regarding data availability, latency, and system capabilities ("The Art of the Possible").

 * Conduct demonstrations and briefings to Senior Executives and Officers to showcase capability delivery.

Quality Assurance & Data Governance

 * Ensure delivered solutions are "fit-for-purpose," validating that the technical output directly addresses the business problem.

 * Champion data quality initiatives, identifying and remediating data integrity issues at the source or transformation layer.

Selection Criteria (Skills & Experience)
Essential Technical Skills

 * Enterprise Data Platforms: Deep expertise in designing solutions on Massively Parallel Processing (MPP) platforms, specifically Teradata.

 * Visualisation Mastery: Expert-level knowledge of Power BI, including complex DAX, data modelling, and Enterprise Gateway configuration.

 * Data Integration: Proven experience architecting ETL/ELT pipelines to collate data from complex, siloed, and legacy systems (e.g., ERP, Logistics, HR systems).

 * Methodology: Strong practical application of Agile/Scrum methodologies within a rigid governance framework (e.g., Defence/Government).

Leadership & Soft Skills

 * Translation Capability: Exceptional ability to communicate complex data concepts (lineage, latency, granularity) to non-technical audiences.

 * Squad Leadership: Proven experience leading technical squads, conducting code reviews, and mentoring developers.

 * Problem Solving: Strategic thinking with the ability to navigate ambiguity and design solutions in a highly regulated environment.

Qualifications & Prerequisites

 * Education: Tertiary qualifications in Computer Science, Data Engineering, Information Management, or equivalent professional experience.

How to Apply

Please submit your CV and a brief cover letter specifying the role(s) you wish to be considered for. Shortlisted applicants will be contacted for further assessment.

Why Sunstone?

People are at the core of Sunstone. We prioritise human connections and collaborations, supported by: 

·       Ongoing training, development, and coaching 

·       Flexible working arrangements tailored to your needs 

·       Broader networking and community involvement opportunities 

Our culture is collaborative, supportive, and professional. At Sunstone, you'll join a highly skilled, experienced team where talent, work ethic, and shared values are recognised and rewarded. 

Sunstone are offering very attractive contractor rates. We offer flexitime and remote work when possible.

Veterans are encouraged to apply.

We are committed to building inclusive cultures in the Australian Government and Defence sectors that respect and promote human rights and diversity. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples are encouraged to apply.

To find out more about Sunstone Advisory visit: www.sunstoneadvisory.com.au

Category: Corporate Finance & Investment Banking (Banking & Financial Services)
Ad Text:
Our client is an infrastructure investor undertaking an exciting period of growth. We’re seeking Corporate Finance talent to join a sponsor-side team delivering large renewal projects under a concession/lease-based model. 

This role is responsible for assisting in deal origination and end-to-end transaction execution across a portfolio of complex infrastructure transactions. You will be experienced in bid processes, including legal/commercial, capital raising, financial and tax structuring and due diligence oversight.

To be successful you will be highly numerate (with strong modelling skill), have sound judgement and have exceptional attention to detail. 

Tertiary qualifications in Commerce / Business/ Law combined with postgraduate (CFA) highly desirable. Experience in a transactional environment such advisory or banking, sponsor or investment management experience, ideally within the economic infrastructure sector preferred.

Please apply online using the links below.  For more information call Niky Ablethorpe on +61 422 469 202. All discussions will be in strict confidence.

About Profectus

Profectus’ Core Values are Trust, Integrity, Relationships, Teamwork, Innovation and Results.

Profectus exists to Deliver extraordinary compliance and analytical solutions that enrich organisations and aspires to Embed Commercial Truth to Fuel the World of Business. Profectus aims to reach its’ new Vision by transforming its’ Operating Model through the Technology Roadmap and aiming to achieve an “Augmented Machine Learning” future state.

Your new role

We are seeking an experienced Senior Data Engineer to design, deliver, and continuously improve reliable, scalable, and secure data solutions across the organisation. In this role, you will ensure timely and accurate data availability, strengthen data governance and automation, and provide technical leadership to uplift our data engineering capability.

Working closely with operational and technology teams, you’ll balance “build fast” with “build right,” supporting urgent business needs while contributing to a long-term strategic data roadmap.

Some of the key duties of this role include:

Design, build, optimise, and maintain scalable, secure, and high-performance data pipelines and architectures across multiple platforms.

Provide timely, up-to-date data to business teams and resolve any process failures within 24 hours.

Implement and enforce data engineering best practices across CI/CD, testing, monitoring, documentation, and version control.

Collaborate closely with analysts, engineers, and operational teams to support data ingestion, accessibility, and quality.

Drive data governance, security, and compliance standards across all data solutions.

Optimise data workflows for performance, scalability, and cost efficiency, reducing technical debt through automation.

Mentor and guide junior data engineers, conduct code reviews, and provide technical leadership.

Contribute to the strategic data roadmap and support delivery of analytics and reporting initiatives.

Work effectively in agile sprints, consistently meeting delivery commitments.

Maintain compliance with technology and cybersecurity policies.

You will have:

Qualifications & Experience

Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.

5+ years’ experience in data engineering, including at least 2 years in a senior role.

Core Technical Skills

Expert knowledge of data architecture, distributed systems, and large-scale data platforms (e.g. Databricks, Snowflake, Spark, Kafka).

Strong experience designing and building data pipelines using technologies such as Databricks, Snowflake, and Azure Data Factory.

Proficiency in Python and other scripting or development languages for data manipulation.

Hands-on experience with relational and non-relational databases (Postgres, MS SQL Server, Redis).

Practical understanding of iPaaS solutions (e.g. Informatica, Fivetran, Boomi).

Strong knowledge of ETL processes, data validation automation, and data lifecycle management.

Experience with Git-based version control and CI/CD practices.

Familiarity with Linux environments and cloud platforms, preferably Azure.

Proven ability to work in agile environments and meet tight delivery deadlines.

Bonus Skills (Nice to Have)

Experience using OpenAI APIs or other LLM platforms.

Exposure to MLOps and deploying data science models into production.

Experience integrating LLMs such as OpenAI (GPT-4/5), Claude, or Llama.

Familiarity with RAG frameworks (LangChain, LlamaIndex, Haystack).

Knowledge of prompt engineering, embeddings, and AI-powered search solutions.

We will offer you

Working at Profectus Group will allow you to enjoy many employee benefits, an inclusive and engaged culture and the opportunity to grow and develop with a clear plan mapped out. Below are some of our benefits:

A values-based workplace, transcending to client interactions 

Variety of employee benefits including paid parental leave, flexible work options and an excellent Employee Assistance Program 

Meaningful learning and development programs that are tailored to your professional development areas/needs 

Quarterly goal setting and review sessions that are linked to company goals

Clear competency frameworks so you know what is expected of you and what skills you require, also identifying any training requirements

Diversity Policy and Working Group, current activity is putting into place a Reconciliation Action Plan

Along with all these wonderful benefits, Profectus Group also has a mentoring program and wellbeing initiatives, including free group personal training sessions and the opportunity to contribute to charity events.

If this sounds like you and you would like more information on the role, please apply today by sending through a copy of your resume and cover letter outlining why we should select you.  

Compliance requirements for this role include Australian Citizenship or Permanent residency and a Police check.

Profectus Group respects people as individuals and values their differences.  It is committed to an inclusive and diverse work environment.  We encourage people from all backgrounds to apply.
